  {
    "uid": 12,
    "id": 14,
    "name": "What Really Happens",
    "wbs": "2.6",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-04-30T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-04-30T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 480,
    "durationWorkingDays": 1,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "This is the procurement reality that many General Contractors find themselves in when they commit to aggressive construction schedules that sidestep real constraints and logic, as with the \"Happy Path\" schedule above. They think they can force things through a process but they fail to understand that when they compress procurement logic, large amounts of risk is introduced into the system. They almost always lose."
  },
