    "notes": "Contractor completes hasty review before sending off to the structural engineer."
  },
  {
    "uid": 18,
    "id": 22,
    "name": "Abbreviated Parallel Multidisciplinary Review",
    "wbs": "3.7",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-07-20T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-07-20T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 480,
    "durationWorkingDays": 1,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "Multidisciplinary reviews get skipped in favor of keeping the process moving quickly."
  },
  {
    "uid": 19,
    "id": 23,
    "name": "GC Submits to Structural Eng. W/ Request to Expedite Review",
    "wbs": "3.8",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-07-21T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-07-21T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 480,
    "durationWorkingDays": 1,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": null
  },
  {
    "uid": 20,
    "id": 24,
    "name": "Reviewer/Approver Review",
    "wbs": "3.9",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-07-22T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-08-11T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 7200,
    "durationWorkingDays": 15,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "GC submits with a demand for expedited review explain that the start of fabrication has already been missed. The structural engineer has 15 days for review, contractually, but the GC asks for a 10-day turnaround. Due to already being overloaded by previous demands for expedited reviews, the engineer is experiencing overload already. Not knowing what is truly important, the engineer promises to do the best that he can and ends up taking the full 15 days."
  },
  {
    "uid": 21,
    "id": 25,
    "name": "Revise & Resubmit Response",
    "wbs": "3.10",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-08-12T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-08-12T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 480,
    "durationWorkingDays": 1,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "Much to the frustration of the GC, the submittal, they  assumed would be returned as \"Approved\", or, \"Approved as Noted\", get returned as \"Revise and Resubmit\". It is obvious that the structural engineer really drilled in on the first 10-15 pages of the shop drawings and red-marked many conflicts and mistakes. After those initial pages, though, the notations decreased. In reality, the engineer, feeling the pressure to get the drawings off their desk, and growing increasingly frustrated with the lack of coordination, simply sent the drawings back for the steel subcontractor to fix everything before submitting again. Now, the GC sends the drawings back to the subcontractor with a fevered demand for a quick turn-around."
  },
  {
    "uid": 22,
    "id": 26,
    "name": "Steel Contractor Starts Revisions",
    "wbs": "3.11",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-08-13T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-08-17T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 1440,
    "durationWorkingDays": 3,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "The steel contractor dives back into the drawings, feeling the heat, and quickly re-discovers the initial questions about design that they had before they started the process. They go back to the GC and demand that the GC run interference and help ge the questions resolved before they start making revisions. Tempers flare. The fabrication start date is long gone and it's become painfully obvious to everyone that the steel is going to be really late."
  },
  {
    "uid": 38,
    "id": 27,
    "name": "Design Questions Pile Up",
    "wbs": "3.12",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-08-18T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-09-09T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 8160,
    "durationWorkingDays": 17,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "The steel contractor submits a lengthy list of RFI's and the GC quickly dumps them onto the design team. The Architect is involved because architecture directly interfaces with the structural steel. It turns out that the missing design for several of the rooms in the house needs to be completed before the Architect can comment on structural issues. The decision is made to push ahead and carefully plan the field work to match the steel, when it eventually shows up. The GC instructs the steel contractor to move forward with revised shop drawings."
  },
  {
    "uid": 23,
    "id": 28,
    "name": "Steel Contractor Pushes to Finalize Submittal",
    "wbs": "3.13",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-09-10T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-10-07T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 9600,
    "durationWorkingDays": 20,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "The steel contractor moves ahead with revised drawings. Since design is still trying to catch up, they make many assumptions that they expect the GC to adhere to. The pressure continues mounting and relationships are becoming strained. Finally, the steel contractor sends the drawings back to the GC. "
  },
  {
    "uid": 41,
    "id": 29,
    "name": "Original Steel Onsite Date",
    "wbs": "3.14",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-10-07T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-10-07T08:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 0,
    "durationWorkingDays": 0,
    "isMilestone": true,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "This is the original date that steel was required to be onsite. The GC committed to this date. It fly's by and the pressure spikes."
  },
  {
    "uid": 24,
    "id": 30,
    "name": "GC Resubmits to Reviewer/Approver",
    "wbs": "3.15",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-10-08T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-10-08T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 480,
    "durationWorkingDays": 1,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "Once again, in the heat of the battle, the GC performs little to no internal review before submitting to the engineer."
  },
  {
    "uid": 25,
    "id": 31,
    "name": "REV 1 Reviewer/Approver Review",
    "wbs": "3.16",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-10-09T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-10-22T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 4800,
    "durationWorkingDays": 10,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "The GC submits again, with a demand for expedited review. The GC explains that this package is now the hottest item on their desk and it is destroying the schedule. Tempers flare as the engineer tells the GC that it is not their fault and they need time to review without the constant pressure of \"everything will be late if you don't hurry\". "
  },
  {
    "uid": 26,
    "id": 32,
    "name": "REV 1 Submittal - Revise & Resubmit",
    "wbs": "3.17",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-10-23T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-10-23T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 480,
    "durationWorkingDays": 1,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "Once again, the GC recieves a \"Revise and Resubmit\" response. About this time, the GC is feeling like the process is hopeless. It seems there are more notations that the first round. Now angry, the GC sends the set back to the steel contractor and blows up. The steel contractor had already communicated that the fabrication window they had reserved  was gone and due their current workload, they would have to fit the GC's project in where they could. This simly meant that the steel sub was experiencing the same issues across their other projects with other GC's and they would figure it out when the time came. Still, the pressure is intense now and every day lost is felt by everyone."
  },
  {
    "uid": 27,
    "id": 33,
    "name": "Submitter Preps REV 2 Submittal",
    "wbs": "3.18",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-10-26T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-11-06T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 4800,
    "durationWorkingDays": 10,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "The steel contactor turns the revised drawings around in 10 days and the GC submits again."
  },
  {
    "uid": 29,
    "id": 34,
    "name": "GC Resubmits to Reviewer/Approver",
    "wbs": "3.19",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-11-09T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-11-09T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 480,
    "durationWorkingDays": 1,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "The GC submits again, with an expedited review request."
  },
  {
    "uid": 30,
    "id": 35,
    "name": "REV 2 Reviewer/Approver Review",
    "wbs": "3.20",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-11-10T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-11-18T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 3360,
    "durationWorkingDays": 7,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": null
  },
  {
    "uid": 31,
    "id": 36,
    "name": "REV 2 Submittal - Approved",
    "wbs": "3.21",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-11-19T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-11-19T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 480,
    "durationWorkingDays": 1,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "The engineer, in spite of finding more problems, finally approves but the approval is \"Approved as Noted\". It should have been \"Revise and Resubmit\" but at some point, the project needs to move forward. Further risk is transferred back to the GC and steel"
  },
  {
    "uid": 32,
    "id": 37,
    "name": "Procurement Authorized",
    "wbs": "3.22",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-11-20T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2026-11-20T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 480,
    "durationWorkingDays": 1,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "The GC sends the drawings back to the steel subcontractor with an urgent message to start fabrication now!"
  },
  {
    "uid": 33,
    "id": 38,
    "name": "Material/Product & Fabrication Lead-Time",
    "wbs": "3.23",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2026-11-23T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2027-01-22T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 21600,
    "durationWorkingDays": 45,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "Shockingly, the steel contractor is able to get to work immediately and tells the GC that they can honor their original, 45-day, fabrication duration. They push ahead and try to capture all the changes that came back noted. The GC has not had the time to coordinate all of the changes in the field, and frankly, doesn't understand the impacts. They move ahead with work in the field based on the \"latest\" shop drawings."
  },
  {
    "uid": 34,
    "id": 39,
    "name": "Trucking/Shipping",
    "wbs": "3.24",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2027-01-25T08:00:00",
    "finish": "2027-01-29T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 2400,
    "durationWorkingDays": 5,
    "isMilestone": false,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": null
  },
  {
    "uid": 35,
    "id": 40,
    "name": "Material/Product Arrives Onsite",
    "wbs": "3.25",
    "outlineLevel": 2,
    "start": "2027-01-29T17:00:00",
    "finish": "2027-01-29T17:00:00",
    "durationMinutes": 0,
    "durationWorkingDays": 0,
    "isMilestone": true,
    "isSummary": false,
    "isCritical": false,
    "notes": "Steel FINALLY arrives onsite. The steel crews mobilize and get to work. Soon, everything stops. The GC and the steel contractor find immediate problems with things like embeds not matching base plates, steel alignment issues, beams that are too long, posts that are too short. This is when the real problems start and the team explodes. The GC wants to blame the steel contractor but the steel contractor pushes back with \"We did waht you tolsd us to do\". Then, the engineers get involved because the GC tries to figure out solutions thst do not involve sending the steel package bcak to the shop for another round of changes. Problems compound on top of each other, fast. This is just the beginning."
  },
